  "text": "For trips within Germany (Regime A), our best-fit gives us a scaling exponent of α = 1.44, which is proximate to that found for Foursquare data (α = 1.50) [CITATION_1] , and for the Where's George data (α = 1.59) [CITATION_2] , though not as near to that found using call data records (α = 1.75) [CITATION_3] . Similar to trips without overnight travel (Fig. 1a ), this is truncated by the diameter of Germany (∼ 10 2.83 km).",
